<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The arguement still is that it is not your guilds fault that they refuse to go back and reraid content to get the rest of it's members flagged for where they are currently able to hunt.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's not so simple as just going back and getting that mob. Here's all the factors that a guild leader needs to consider when picking targets:<br>
<br>
1) What is up. These flag mobs aren't instant repops. They may not be up.<br>
2) What other guilds are doing. You don't raid in a vacuum - if Explicit decides that first thing on a given day they're killing Aerin'Dar, well, then we aren't getting anyone flagged for HoH that day unless Explicit lets them tag along. Given that there's four different guilds that are actively doing PoP flag raids, that means it can be 12 days between kills on a given flag mob (3 day repop).<br>
3) Who has what flags. If you have 58 people online who need flag B, which requires flag A, and only two people online that need flag A, which are you going to do? Remember, all these people are part-time players - if you don't do flag B now, you will run into the exact same problem flagging all these 60 people for B. You try and flag maximal numbers of people every raid just to get it over with. That's what really leads to people being left far behind.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It is not the guilds fault that sooner or later it would realize that now they would need to go back ang flag its members so that they have enough to continue raiding.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, at the very least the raid force that completed flag X-1 can always raid for flag X if they're all online!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I have no sympathy for any member of any guild that HAS to be the first to do something. HAS to be the first to obtain the awesome gear. HAS to be the first to say &quot;hey, we did this with only half our members&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Heh, you know the real reason to do something first? So that it's waiting for you after all other targets are exhausted. Being the only guild in any place is a tremendous advantage, one that's very worthwhile. It's not about the gear so much as it is having something enjoyable to do whenever you log on.<br>
<br>
And bragging about doing more with less? Some people are into that. Personally, I don't care as long as the fights aren't sloppy zergfests with people being thrown into mobs like cannon fodder. In my opinion the smartest thing I've ever seen Gurunt say on an EZBoard forum was when he said &quot;Who cares how many it takes, all that matters is it dies&quot; when talking about the Emperor.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I understand your logic now. Thank you for enlightening me.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, you're adding your own spin to things. You WANT to dislike the people in top raiding guilds, perhaps based on what you've read on other guild pages. If we were as disagreeable as Fires of Heaven, I'd agree with you. But we aren't. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :crush --><img src=http://www.quellious-collective.com/emoticons/crush.gif ALT=":crush"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If the members of your guild were so concerned about not being able to raid with the rest of the guild, why not say something to the guild about it? And if their answer is... &quot;oh well&quot; that tells ya what kind of guild you are in.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
We do. And the answer isn't &quot;oh, well&quot;. Our guildmates that can get every flag are just as frustrated as those of us that can't be online for every kill. We have students, parents, businessmen, and people from Britain to Australia in our guild. Trying to schedule kills so we beat other guilds to them (so we can actually kill the mobs) AND get everyone flagged is a massive headache. The nature of flags prior to today's patch, where you required previous flags to get subsequent flags, made it even worse.<br>
<br>
