<br>
it used to be that playing 50 hours a week was enough.  if you missed mondays raid the big loss was you werent there for monday =).   if you still played 50 hours that week gtg.  rock on.<br>
<br>
now however.  its not only how much you play but *always* being available to play.   here always derived from if your goal is never to be behind.  before 50 hours primetimish was enough to insure you arnt behind.  now its not becuase if you work 1 late nite a week and its a key raid  your behind nevermind if you played even 60 hours that week.  its a shift of the life style verant wants you to have.   its a shift from just play alot to be available always.<br>
<br>
and in shifting the lifestyle you need to have to being available to raid every week nite and weekend if you dont want to play catchup,  SoE has shrunk its user base.   the next few months should be interesting.<br>
<br>
personally i think they will fold. this will be written off as an experiment in 3 months.<br>
